{"stances":[{"url":"https://www.merx.com/public/supplier/solicitations/notice/22784937100/abstract","stance":"contradicts","quote":"This requirement is open only to those Electrical & Electronic Products Supply Arrangement Holders who qualified under Stream two (2) for services in the National Capital Region for the following category: 1. Stream two (2) – Electronic Products Following SA Holders have been invited to submit a proposal"},{"url":"https://www.merx.com/public/supplier/solicitations/notice/22784996660/abstract","stance":"supports","quote":"Shared Services Canada (SSC) has a requirement for Raritan Power Distribution Units and Vertiv Racks, or equivalent"},{"url":"https://www.it-beschaffung.ch/564/beschaffung-von-stromverteilereinheiten-pdu","stance":"supports","quote":"Marktabklärungen zeigten, dass nur eine Firma PDU anbieten kann... Die Vergabe an die Firma Riedo Networks AG erfolgt somit freihändig"},{"url":"https://www.utahbids.net/bid-result/enlogic_power_distribution_units-14182081","stance":"supports","quote":"Intellivex Data Center Solutions is the apparent low bidder on the University of Utah - Purchasing's Enlogic Power Distribution Units solicitation, with a low bid of $129,775.09 USD"},{"url":"https://prospeo.io/s/serviceable-obtainable-market","stance":"supports","quote":"SOM is the revenue you can realistically capture in 1-3 years. Not a fantasy percentage of SAM."},{"url":"https://vcbeast.com/compare/sam-vs-som","stance":"contradicts","quote":"Typical SOM is 1-5% of SAM for early-stage companies, growing as the company scales."},{"url":"https://icanpitch.com/blog/tam-sam-som-market-sizing-guide","stance":"supports","quote":"3-5%

Realistic SOM

Market share in 3-5 years"}],"status":"contested","statusRationale":"The tender evidence partly supports the hypothesis: the Zurich CHF 1.996M PDU procurement was explicitly sole-sourced (freihändig) on grounds only one firm qualified, and multiple standalone PDU tenders are small and single-model/spec-locked ('No substitutions', 'or equivalent' but naming Vertiv/Raritan/Enlogic). This corroborates the near-non-contestable characterization. The benchmark-semantics leg is strongly supported: Prospeo defines SOM as 1-3 years and VC Beast/ICanPitch as 3-5 years multi-year cumulative — so a 1% figure treated as Year-1 is aspirational. However, the SOM sources uniformly state 1-5% (or 3-5%) as the typical band, directly contradicting the claim that benchmarks 'point below the band.' Also the surfaced Zurich tender (CHF ~2M) and DND multi-holder invitations undercut the claim that only tiny ($58K-$130K) standalone procurements exist and that pools are always non-contestable. The load-bearing zero-margin bundling mechanism itself is neither confirmed nor denied by any result — no source shows PDUs priced at zero margin inside integrated packages. Evidence is mixed on both legs; no load-bearing premise is directly refuted, but non-load-bearing links (size/contestability of pool, benchmark direction) are credibly challenged.","evidence":[{"title":"Beschaffung von Stromverteilereinheiten (PDU) — Direct Award, Stadt Zürich","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"it-beschaffung.ch / Stadt Zürich OIZ","date":"2024-07-04","excerpt":"Beschaffung von 900 Stromverteilereinheiten... Awards: Riedo Networks AG CHF 1,996,000. Marktabklärungen zeigten, dass nur eine Firma PDU anbieten kann... Die Vergabe erfolgt somit freihändig.","url":"https://www.it-beschaffung.ch/564/beschaffung-von-stromverteilereinheiten-pdu"},{"title":"Serviceable Obtainable Market (SOM): How to Calculate It","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"Prospeo","date":null,"excerpt":"SOM is the revenue you can realistically capture in 1-3 years. Not a fantasy percentage of SAM.","url":"https://prospeo.io/s/serviceable-obtainable-market"},{"title":"SAM vs SOM: Key Differences Explained","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"VC Beast","date":"2026-03-13","excerpt":"SOM is the portion of SAM you can realistically capture in a defined time period (usually 3-5 years)... Typical SOM is 1-5% of SAM for early-stage companies.","url":"https://vcbeast.com/compare/sam-vs-som"}],"revisedLikelihood":0.38,"revisionRationale":"Evidence cuts both ways. The sole-sourced Zurich PDU award and spec-locked single-model tenders support the non-contestability and bundling-adjacent thesis, and the SOM-is-multi-year semantics are confirmed. But the surfaced CHF ~2M standalone PDU deal directly undercuts the 'only tiny ($58K-$130K)' claim, and the SOM sources reaffirm 1-5%/3-5% bands rather than pointing below 0.5%. The core zero-margin bundling mechanism remains unevidenced. Net effect is a marginal downward revision from 0.4 reflecting mixed corroboration."}
